stylometry: A genetic algorithm is an intelligent method of exploring all possible outcomes for a problem and returning a good (but not necessarily optimal) solution.  Genetic algorithms explore branches of a solution to find one that works well, but might not necessarily solve the problem all the way through during this exploration.  Evolutionary solver is important for solving non-linear problems because it utilizes a genetic algorithm to explore possible solutions.  If we only used conventional solver for non-linear, we might get an incorrect solution involving local maxima or minima.
